23-02-02 |website=Wikipedia, The Free Encyclopedia |publisher=[[Wikimedia Foundation]]}}</ref> and newsletters of specific [[WikiProject|WikiProjects]] like ''The Bugle'' from WikiProject Military History<ref>{{Cite web |title=Wikipedia:WikiProject Military history/Open tasks - News |url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Military_history/Open_tasks |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Wikipedia, The Free Encyclopedia |publisher=[[Wikimedia Foundation]]}}</ref> and the monthly newsletter from The Guild of Copy Editors.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Wikipedia:WikiProject Guild of Copy Editors/Newsletters |url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Guild_of_Copy_Editors/Newsletters |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Wikipedia, The Free Encyclopedia |publisher=[[Wikimedia Foundation]]}}</ref> There are also several publications from the [[Wikimedia Foundation]] and multilingual publications such as Wikimedia Diff<ref>{{Cite web |title=Wikimedia Diff - News from across the Wikimedia movement |url=https://diff.wikimedia.org/ |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Wikimedia Diff |publisher=[[Wikimedia Foundation]]}}</ref> and ''This Month in Education''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=This Month in Education |url=https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Education/News |access-date=2023-02-02 |website=Wikimedia Meta-Wiki |publisher=[[Wikimedia Foundation]]}}</ref>\n[[File:Wikipedia Library owl.svg|thumb|Wikipedia Library]]\n\n=== The Wikipedia Library ===\n{{for|information for Wikipedia editors|Wikipedia:The Wikipedia Library|selfref=yes}}\nThe Wikipedia Library is a resource for Wikipedia editors which provides free access to a wide range of [[Electronic publishing|digital publications]], so that they can consult and cite these while editing the encyclopedia.<ref name="orlowitz">{{cite journal |last1=Orlowitz |first1=Jake |date=January 2018 |title=The Wikipedia Library : the biggest encyclopedia needs a digital library and we are building it |url=https://www.researchgate.net/pub